# Phase 4: Scoring Aggregation & Results Dashboard

Phase 4 consumes the evaluation results produced by Phase 3's 5-pillar GUIDE engine and presents them in a stunning, professional Results Dashboard. This includes backend aggregation APIs and a feature-rich frontend visualization with radar charts, metric breakdowns, session ranking, and score trends.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — Dashboard API Layer

---

#### [NEW] [dashboard_schema.py](file:///d:/Project/Final_Year_Project/Interview_with_AI/app/schemas/dashboard_schema.py)

Pydantic models for dashboard-specific API responses:

- **`SessionSummary`** — Lightweight session card: `session_id`, `composite_q_score`, `pillar_scores` dict, `created_at`, `duration_minutes`, `total_events`
- **`DashboardStats`** — Aggregate statistics: `total_sessions`, `average_q_score`, `highest_q_score`, `lowest_q_score`, `pillar_averages` dict, `score_distribution` (histogram buckets)
- **`RankingEntry`** — Ranking row: `rank`, `session_id`, `composite_q_score`, `pillar_scores`, `created_at`
- **`DashboardResponse`** — API envelope with `stats`, `recent_sessions`, `rankings`

---

#### [NEW] [dashboard_service.py](file:///d:/Project/Final_Year_Project/Interview_with_AI/app/services/dashboard_service.py)

Business logic for aggregation and scoring:

- **`get_dashboard_stats()`** — MongoDB aggregation pipeline to compute: total sessions, average/max/min Q scores, average per-pillar scores, score distribution buckets (0-20, 20-40, 40-60, 60-80, 80-100)
- **`get_session_rankings(limit, sort_by, order)`** — Sorted evaluations with rank numbering, supporting sort by `composite_q_score` or any pillar score
- **`get_session_detail(session_id)`** — Full evaluation detail for a single session including all 19 metrics, pillar breakdowns, and session metadata
- **`get_score_trends(limit)`** — Chronological session scores for trend visualization

---

#### [NEW] [dashboard_routes.py](file:///d:/Project/Final_Year_Project/Interview_with_AI/app/routes/dashboard_routes.py)

API endpoints:

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
